WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:04.221
-[siren wails in distance]
-You are gonna sleep.

00:04.265 --> 00:05.701
You hear me?

00:08.921 --> 00:10.097
[sighs]

00:13.709 --> 00:16.059
Sleep like the damn dead.

00:16.103 --> 00:18.105
♪

00:28.332 --> 00:31.901
MARTIN:
Malcolm, I want you
to remember something.

00:31.944 --> 00:33.685
YOUNG BRIGHT:
Dad!

00:33.729 --> 00:35.078
MARTIN:
We're the same.

00:39.474 --> 00:41.432
JESSICA:
You look exhausted.

00:41.476 --> 00:43.521
-Not sleeping will do that.
-Night terrors?

00:43.565 --> 00:45.306
BRIGHT:
I've been seeing new things.

00:45.349 --> 00:47.438
It's like my subconscious
is trying to show me something.

00:47.482 --> 00:49.310
-Like what?
-Lost memories.

00:49.353 --> 00:51.747
Your father's things
are off-limits!

00:51.790 --> 00:54.532
BRIGHT: Malcolm, when was the last time you slept through the night?

00:54.576 --> 00:56.752
BRIGHT:
Tell me about
the girl in the box.

00:56.795 --> 00:59.537
-There wasn't any girl.
-There was no girl in a box.

00:59.581 --> 01:02.149
JESSICA:
Nightmares aren't real.
Neither was she.

01:04.064 --> 01:06.066
♪

01:13.073 --> 01:14.422
[sniffles]

01:30.351 --> 01:32.353
♪

01:47.237 --> 01:50.197
[woman whimpering faintly]

01:55.637 --> 01:58.248
[faint whimpering continues]

01:58.292 --> 02:00.163
Hello?

02:01.208 --> 02:02.600
[woman crying]

02:02.644 --> 02:04.602
You okay?

02:04.646 --> 02:06.604
[crying continues]

02:08.128 --> 02:09.999
Hey!

02:10.042 --> 02:12.436
Hey, I need some help! Hey!

02:12.480 --> 02:15.265
[barking]

02:15.309 --> 02:17.180
Hey, bro. Back away from my car.

02:19.443 --> 02:20.792
I said move!

02:20.836 --> 02:23.360
-Sorry. I just, I, uh...
-[barking continues]

02:23.404 --> 02:26.015
[panting]:
I just...

02:26.058 --> 02:29.149
need sleep.

02:36.243 --> 02:37.853
[door opens]

02:39.289 --> 02:40.595
Good morning.

02:40.638 --> 02:43.075
Don't lie to your mother.
You look exhausted.

02:43.119 --> 02:44.642
If I have to bring you
to the hospital,

02:44.686 --> 02:45.861
my whole morning will be shot.

02:45.904 --> 02:48.864
[sighs] You don't
have to worry about me.

02:48.907 --> 02:50.257
[scoffs]

02:50.300 --> 02:53.042
What are you so busy with?

02:53.085 --> 02:55.827
I am taking meetings
for my charitable work.

02:55.871 --> 02:59.091
I've been thinking
that maybe you were right.

02:59.135 --> 03:01.093
-Impossible.
-[laughs]

03:01.137 --> 03:03.313
I shouldn't be so cloak-
and-dagger with my donations.

03:03.357 --> 03:06.273
My family's foundation was once
a formidable force for good.

03:06.316 --> 03:09.667
I have put out calls
to some wonderful nonprofits

03:09.711 --> 03:12.453
who would really benefit
from my...

03:12.496 --> 03:14.063
-Cash?
-[chuckles]

03:14.106 --> 03:15.325
Precisely. [chuckles]

03:15.369 --> 03:16.413
[sighs]

03:20.461 --> 03:22.071
Talk to me.

03:24.291 --> 03:25.901
About what?

03:27.294 --> 03:29.034
You've always listened
to my issues.

03:29.078 --> 03:30.471
I want to be here for yours.

03:31.472 --> 03:33.474
These nightmares, your...

03:34.475 --> 03:36.912
...memories,

03:36.955 --> 03:38.914
they're getting worse?

03:38.957 --> 03:43.484
Yes. They are becoming
more vivid.

03:43.527 --> 03:46.269
I haven't slept in days.

03:46.313 --> 03:50.882
Well... what you clearly need
is an epic nap.

03:50.926 --> 03:52.275
What's your take
on barbiturates?

03:52.319 --> 03:53.450
Personally, I'm a fan.

03:53.494 --> 03:55.322
Only one thing seems to help me.

03:55.365 --> 03:56.497
Hmm.

03:56.540 --> 03:58.107
I need a murder.

03:58.150 --> 04:00.152
-[sighs] -GIL: I can't help you, Bright.

04:00.196 --> 04:01.850
Come on.
There has to be something.

04:01.893 --> 04:03.504
Nothing that requires
a profiler.

04:03.547 --> 04:06.289
No murders, no kinks, no boiling
bunnies, nothing deviant at all?

04:06.333 --> 04:07.508
This is New York.

04:07.551 --> 04:09.292
You okay?

04:09.336 --> 04:11.512
I'm amazing. Top of the world.

04:11.555 --> 04:12.774
Because you look like hell.

04:12.817 --> 04:14.471
And that off-the-charts
manic thing you do?

04:14.515 --> 04:16.778
-It's off the charts.
-JT: Hey, boss.

04:16.821 --> 04:19.128
-Need a ride?
-I'll catch up.

04:19.171 --> 04:21.130
Hey. You look horrible.

04:21.173 --> 04:23.350
I know, right?
Where are they going?

04:23.393 --> 04:24.699
-It's not your thing.
-You don't know that.

04:24.742 --> 04:26.483
I'm into all sorts of things.

04:26.527 --> 04:28.746
It's a drug hit,
double homicide.

04:28.790 --> 04:31.923
-And I don't need a profiler.
-I hear you. I do.

04:31.967 --> 04:34.317
But would you believe
that homicide

04:34.361 --> 04:37.146
appears to be the only thing
keeping me sane?

04:40.018 --> 04:42.804
Solving, not doing.

04:42.847 --> 04:44.632
I need this.

04:47.548 --> 04:48.984
[car horn blares]

04:49.027 --> 04:51.029
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

04:51.073 --> 04:52.509
What's he doing here?

04:52.553 --> 04:55.512
Hey! Detective Tarmel.
How about that game last night?

04:55.556 --> 04:57.514
-Exciting stuff.
-Which game?

04:57.558 --> 05:00.082
Oh, you know, the game,
with the players.

05:01.605 --> 05:03.564
Forget it.
I'll show myself to the body.

05:03.607 --> 05:05.217
No, you won't.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.352
What's the matter?
You don't see it?

05:10.397 --> 05:11.659
Allow me.

05:13.748 --> 05:15.706
BRIGHT:
Huh. A speakeasy.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.360
Cool.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.535
What are you doing here?

05:18.579 --> 05:20.972
I was in the neighborhood.

05:21.016 --> 05:22.583
What do we have?

05:22.626 --> 05:24.846
Two vics, starting here
with the-- let's be honest--

05:24.889 --> 05:26.587
crappy bodyguard.

05:26.630 --> 05:29.372
His throat was slashed, and his
boss didn't get off any easier.

05:29.416 --> 05:32.549
JT: Our human snow globe:
Jacques Desir, 34,

05:32.593 --> 05:34.029
of Haitian descent,

05:34.072 --> 05:36.640
known pusher of molly,
other high-end party drugs,

05:36.684 --> 05:38.425
and, yes, cocaine.

05:38.468 --> 05:40.775
DANI: He controlled
New York's Haitian dealers.

05:40.818 --> 05:42.994
Ruthless but respected.

05:43.038 --> 05:44.387
Allow me.

05:45.823 --> 05:47.477
Ruthless.

05:49.044 --> 05:52.395
Someone cut out his tongue.

05:52.439 --> 05:54.615
And you said you didn't need me.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.051
Talk to me, Powell.

05:56.094 --> 05:57.748
Desir controlled
most of Flatbush.

05:57.792 --> 05:59.837
But there is a contested section
of Ditmas Avenue

05:59.881 --> 06:01.448
that the Trinitarios
have been trying to get

06:01.491 --> 06:02.449
for the Dominicans.

06:02.492 --> 06:04.320
It's an ongoing beef.

06:04.364 --> 06:05.974
And the Trinitarios answer to?

06:06.017 --> 06:07.323
Saulo Reyes.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.455
If the Dominicans
are responsible,

06:08.498 --> 06:09.717
Saulo is in the know.

06:16.680 --> 06:18.421
Desir's guys may be looking
to hit back hard.

06:18.465 --> 06:19.596
If we're not quick
with a collar...

06:19.640 --> 06:21.076
We got ourselves a drug war.

06:21.119 --> 06:23.992
Are we sure this is about drugs?

06:24.035 --> 06:26.821
He's literally covered in drugs.

06:26.864 --> 06:29.476
Yeah, forget about that for
a second. This happened fast.

06:29.519 --> 06:31.869
Desir didn't even have enough
time to get out of his chair.

06:31.913 --> 06:33.654
He must have been surprised.

06:33.697 --> 06:36.091
Well, he paid that guy
good money to not be surprised.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.834
Whoever did this,
Desir let them get close.

06:39.877 --> 06:41.618
You think our killer
was a friend?

06:41.662 --> 06:44.708
Possibly. At the very least,
Desir trusted them.

06:44.752 --> 06:46.493
Bro, this was an execution.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.019
Why did they cut out his tongue?

06:51.062 --> 06:53.500
DANI:
Psychological warfare.

06:53.543 --> 06:54.849
Cartels have been using it
since the '80s.

06:54.892 --> 06:56.677
But this isn't cartel.

06:56.720 --> 06:59.331
You said yourself this is
street level, a turf dispute.

07:00.681 --> 07:02.509
How much cocaine is this?

07:03.684 --> 07:07.296
Maybe a kilo? It looks uncut.

07:07.339 --> 07:10.691
-20K, give or take.
-You did a stint in Narcotics.

07:10.734 --> 07:12.170
Get to the point.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.086
If this was a drug hit,
strictly business,

07:15.130 --> 07:17.698
then why did the killer dump
$20,000 worth of product

07:17.741 --> 07:18.873
on a dead guy?

07:18.916 --> 07:20.918
Seems like bad business.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.920
No, this was driven by anger.

07:22.964 --> 07:25.357
-Like a vengeance killing.
-Mm-mm.

07:25.401 --> 07:28.099
Desir's crew was tight.
This is about turf or product.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.711
Oh, I'm not the expert
that you are...

07:30.754 --> 07:32.713
Oh, look at that.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.149
We finally agree on something.

07:34.192 --> 07:35.367
You're wrong.

07:35.411 --> 07:38.501
We need a sit-down
with the Dominicans.

07:38.545 --> 07:39.676
I'll make the call.

07:39.720 --> 07:41.461
Thank you.

07:43.985 --> 07:45.682
What did I say?

07:45.726 --> 07:47.205
[door opens]

07:47.249 --> 07:49.207
Lay off the Dani profile.

07:49.251 --> 07:51.514
Not everyone's so keen
on revisiting their past.

07:51.558 --> 07:53.385
[door closes]

07:57.999 --> 08:00.175
BRIGHT:
Why are we here?

08:00.218 --> 08:02.177
After the '90s,
gangs and police made a deal

08:02.220 --> 08:03.918
that churches are safe spaces.

08:03.961 --> 08:06.921
Cops like Gil negotiated truces
between them,

08:06.964 --> 08:08.400
saved a lot of lives.

08:16.234 --> 08:18.628
[door opens, closes]

08:20.412 --> 08:22.414
♪

08:37.821 --> 08:38.996
Saulo.

08:40.607 --> 08:42.173
Lieutenant Arroyo.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.175
I can only imagine we're here

08:44.219 --> 08:47.483
to pay our respects
to the late Desir.

08:47.527 --> 08:48.876
Did you do it?

08:51.400 --> 08:54.577
If you ordered Desir killed,
they'll come for you.

08:54.621 --> 08:58.581
You'll lose men and product.
Let me stop them.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.801
I am a legitimate
businessman, Gil.

09:00.844 --> 09:02.585
Off the record, though...

09:04.456 --> 09:05.762
...none of my people
were responsible.

09:05.806 --> 09:07.590
You want Estimé.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.245
He's lying.

09:11.681 --> 09:13.509
Xavier Estimé
was in Desir's camp.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.206
They were friends.

09:15.250 --> 09:17.818
Friends become enemies overnight
in this business.

09:17.861 --> 09:21.256
He's nonviolent.
You know, like you.

09:21.299 --> 09:23.301
Estimé doesn't even
move product.

09:23.345 --> 09:24.651
I don't know who your girl is,

09:24.694 --> 09:26.957
but she's working
off stale intel.

09:27.001 --> 09:29.612
Estimé was Desir's number two.

09:29.656 --> 09:31.527
-With a bullet.
-[chain rattling]

09:31.571 --> 09:34.225
Now, he's number one.

09:34.269 --> 09:35.836
DANI:
That's not true.

09:35.879 --> 09:37.489
If you didn't order the hit,
who did?

09:37.533 --> 09:39.622
-Just give us a name.
-GIL: Powell.

09:39.666 --> 09:42.016
SAULO:
Insubordination is
a dangerous thing.

09:42.059 --> 09:44.192
[woman crying]

09:44.235 --> 09:46.411
...one person has something
to say, then all the other guys

09:46.455 --> 09:47.804
start thinking
they can have an opinion.

09:47.848 --> 09:49.197
-[quietly]: Ignore it.
-[wood creaking]

09:49.240 --> 09:51.503
-Undermine you.
-Ignore it.

09:51.547 --> 09:53.418
Sabotage the whole project.

09:53.462 --> 09:55.595
You and I have
different leadership styles.

09:56.857 --> 09:58.815
[chain rattling]

09:58.859 --> 10:01.513
[echoing]: I wish I could help,
'cause you're right.

10:03.124 --> 10:04.995
This is war.

10:05.039 --> 10:06.475
But it's not my war.

10:06.518 --> 10:07.824
[woman crying faintly]

10:07.868 --> 10:09.826
This was between
Desir and Estimé.

10:10.827 --> 10:11.828
[panting]

10:13.482 --> 10:16.833
Sorry. Sorry.

10:18.313 --> 10:19.880
I-I thought I saw a bug.

10:19.923 --> 10:21.403
I hate bugs.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.058
Who is this?

10:24.101 --> 10:26.843
Mr. Bright is our profiler.

10:28.715 --> 10:30.847
Desir had his tongue cut out.

10:32.109 --> 10:33.720
Why would someone do that?

10:33.763 --> 10:35.025
People are superstitious.

10:35.069 --> 10:37.462
But not you.
You're a religious man.

10:37.506 --> 10:40.727
Catholic. You blessed yourself
before you sat down.

10:40.770 --> 10:43.904
Some cultures believe you remove
a part of the body after death,

10:43.947 --> 10:46.515
you trap the soul
inside it forever.

10:46.558 --> 10:47.951
Damning them to walk the Earth.

10:47.995 --> 10:51.302
That's how you know I've got
nothing to do with this.

10:51.346 --> 10:54.349
I don't need a bunch of ghosts
following me around.

10:59.833 --> 11:01.704
You and me both.

11:05.360 --> 11:06.927
-[phones ringing]
-[sighs]

11:14.848 --> 11:16.371
What are you working on?

11:16.414 --> 11:18.112
My profile.

11:18.155 --> 11:21.550
Saulo's a killer.
You see that, right?

11:21.593 --> 11:22.769
Of course he is.

11:22.812 --> 11:24.901
But he's not Desir's killer.

11:24.945 --> 11:26.947
Neither is Estimé.

11:27.948 --> 11:29.950
So...

11:29.993 --> 11:31.908
if you're thinking
that he fits your profile,

11:31.952 --> 11:33.518
back off.

11:33.562 --> 11:34.955
Tell me why.

11:34.998 --> 11:39.133
Profiles are built
on information.

11:39.176 --> 11:43.180
And right now, our information
points to Estimé.

11:43.224 --> 11:46.183
But I don't know him
like you do.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.750
Or did.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.752
Don't do that.

11:49.796 --> 11:50.927
What?

11:50.971 --> 11:52.363
Profile me.

11:52.407 --> 11:55.236
[sighs]

11:55.279 --> 11:57.760
I want to help you,

11:57.804 --> 12:01.764
but I can't do that
until you help me understand.

12:01.808 --> 12:04.375
I don't know Estimé.

12:04.419 --> 12:05.812
You do.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.859
GIL:
Edrisa's report is in.

12:09.903 --> 12:12.601
The powder on the body
wasn't coke.

12:12.644 --> 12:14.777
Mix of psilocybin and MDMA.

12:14.821 --> 12:17.606
Huh. Mushrooms and ecstasy.

12:17.649 --> 12:20.174
Sounds like a particularly
rousing combination.

12:20.217 --> 12:22.002
Is there anything in there
that will actually help us

12:22.045 --> 12:23.655
catch our killer?

12:23.699 --> 12:26.789
Desir and the bodyguard were
killed with the same blade.

12:26.833 --> 12:28.835
But the spatter pattern
was irregular.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.227
The bodyguard was
covered in blood,

12:30.271 --> 12:31.838
but Desir's chest was clean,
like he was wearing

12:31.881 --> 12:34.928
some kind of outer layer.

12:40.020 --> 12:41.151
Okay.

12:41.195 --> 12:42.457
There's something else.

12:44.067 --> 12:45.808
The bodyguard was killed second.

12:47.854 --> 12:50.465
Uh, the DNA transfer
proves it.

12:50.508 --> 12:53.598
Our killer never went
through security.

12:53.642 --> 12:54.774
Desir knew him.

12:57.037 --> 12:59.822
Like a friend. I think.

13:01.693 --> 13:02.999
We got to talk to Estimé.

13:06.089 --> 13:07.438
Okay.

13:07.482 --> 13:08.831
Let me do it.

13:08.875 --> 13:10.267
No. You're too close to this.

13:10.311 --> 13:13.009
See, I-I think that that,
that is a good thing.

13:13.053 --> 13:14.445
Dani, you're wrong.

13:16.230 --> 13:17.971
Work up a warrant.

13:18.014 --> 13:19.842
When the judge says we're good,

13:19.886 --> 13:22.845
we go in together;
no moves until then.

13:22.889 --> 13:23.846
Everybody got it?

13:25.065 --> 13:26.501
Got it.

13:30.113 --> 13:32.115
[classical music playing]

13:34.944 --> 13:36.598
[calls out]:
Kimberly.

13:39.993 --> 13:42.125
Have Louisa clean all this up.

13:42.169 --> 13:44.693
All of it? There's still time,
if someone's running late.

13:44.736 --> 13:46.695
[sighs]
Let's not fool ourselves.

13:46.738 --> 13:50.046
Four guests, four no-shows.
We all know what this is.

13:50.090 --> 13:53.049
No one wants anything to do
with The Surgeon.

13:53.093 --> 13:55.051
Even though it's my money,
not his.

13:55.095 --> 13:56.661
I can follow up.

13:56.705 --> 13:58.881
That won't be necessary.

13:58.925 --> 14:00.883
I'm sorry, Mrs. Whitly.

14:07.716 --> 14:09.718
WOMAN:
I'll have one,
if you're pouring.

14:09.761 --> 14:11.241
JESSICA:
And you are?

14:11.285 --> 14:13.374
Eve Blanchard.
I'm here for your money.

14:13.417 --> 14:15.593
[laughs]
Ms. Blanchard...

14:15.637 --> 14:17.334
Oh, you won't find me
on that list.

14:17.378 --> 14:18.945
I slipped past your housekeeper.

14:18.988 --> 14:20.511
Not the best security.

14:20.555 --> 14:21.904
I'm an attorney.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.384
I heard your foundation
is looking for

14:23.427 --> 14:25.038
a good cause to invest in.

14:25.081 --> 14:26.561
I hope you don't
mind me crashing.

14:26.604 --> 14:28.041
I prefer a personal approach.

14:28.084 --> 14:30.521
You're an attorney?

14:30.565 --> 14:34.047
I have a rather
particular focus.

14:34.090 --> 14:35.483
I fight human trafficking.

14:35.526 --> 14:37.920
Finding funding isn't easy.

14:37.964 --> 14:39.922
Do you know who
my ex-husband is?

14:39.966 --> 14:41.532
I do.

14:41.576 --> 14:45.145
Hopefully you won't judge me
by my exes either.

14:45.188 --> 14:48.800
I'm looking for a smart partner
with deep pockets.

14:50.367 --> 14:53.936
And if you really are interested
in making a tangible impact

14:53.980 --> 14:57.940
on a global scale,
I'll take that drink.

14:57.984 --> 14:59.811
Rocks?

14:59.855 --> 15:01.074
Neat.

15:01.117 --> 15:02.945
[exhales]

15:02.989 --> 15:05.339
["Old Friend"
by Elderbrook playing]

15:05.382 --> 15:07.950
-[lively chatter]
-♪ And it's just like
an old friend♪

15:07.994 --> 15:09.952
♪ Coming up, yeah,
I know them♪

15:09.996 --> 15:11.954
♪ Drop-top in the driveway♪

15:11.998 --> 15:13.782
♪ Locked up 'cause
it's slow then♪

15:13.825 --> 15:15.088
♪ I've been looking
for problems♪

15:15.131 --> 15:17.394
♪ One look and I'm all in♪

15:17.438 --> 15:19.135
♪ Is it late in the morning?♪

15:19.179 --> 15:21.050
♪ If I fall down,
then I can keep crawling...♪

15:21.094 --> 15:23.052
♪

15:23.096 --> 15:24.619
-Come here often?
-Listen, I'm not--

15:26.012 --> 15:28.797
Damn it, Bright,
what are you doing here?

15:28.840 --> 15:30.973
Can't sleep.
What's your excuse?

15:31.017 --> 15:33.019
This is Estimé's club.

15:33.062 --> 15:34.672
I'm gonna get a lot more
out of Estimé

15:34.716 --> 15:37.327
than 12 dudes with guns
pointed at him.

15:37.371 --> 15:40.156
Well, you wouldn't disobey Gil
unless you had to,

15:40.200 --> 15:42.071
so why do you have to?

15:44.117 --> 15:47.816
The answer is "yes,"
to your bad pickup line.

15:47.859 --> 15:50.166
Yes, I come here often.

15:50.210 --> 15:51.602
At least I-I used to.

15:51.646 --> 15:54.170
You weren't just in Narcotics.
You were undercover.

15:54.214 --> 15:56.172
Two years.

15:56.216 --> 15:58.000
MAN:
Excuse me.

15:58.044 --> 16:01.177
Mr. Estimé would like to
have a word with both of you.

16:01.221 --> 16:05.965
♪ It's in my blood
and bones...♪

16:09.272 --> 16:10.882
Are you sure
that guy's not dangerous?

16:10.926 --> 16:13.015
Because in my experience,
people who lurk

16:13.059 --> 16:15.409
behind giant windows in
nightclubs are up to no good.

16:15.452 --> 16:17.846
You're profiling a window?

16:17.889 --> 16:19.891
That's a bad-guy window.

16:20.936 --> 16:22.242
[door opens]

16:26.942 --> 16:29.249
ESTIMEÉ:
Trini, give us the room.

16:31.642 --> 16:32.992
Come on, girls.

16:36.299 --> 16:39.041
-[quietly]: There's a lot
of drugs in that box.
-It's fine.

16:45.308 --> 16:47.919
-ESTIMEÉ: It's been a minute.
-[door closes]

16:47.963 --> 16:49.747
You look...

16:49.791 --> 16:52.098
better than the last time
I saw you.

16:53.273 --> 16:54.883
He a cop, too?

16:54.926 --> 16:57.625
We're here about Desir.

16:57.668 --> 17:00.236
Who killed him?

17:00.280 --> 17:02.630
Does it matter?

17:02.673 --> 17:04.066
Everyone thinks it was me.

17:04.110 --> 17:05.198
DANI:
Is everyone right?

17:05.241 --> 17:07.461
I heard you were
his right hand.

17:07.504 --> 17:10.725
Moving product, women.

17:10.768 --> 17:12.944
I told them that's not
the Estimé that I knew.

17:12.988 --> 17:15.077
Come on. Where's my sweet girl?

17:15.121 --> 17:17.123
The one who used to party down.

17:20.517 --> 17:22.084
I had nothing to do with it.

17:24.739 --> 17:29.309
People change,
for better and for worse.

17:29.352 --> 17:30.701
You forget what I did for you?

17:30.745 --> 17:32.181
Why do you think I'm here?

17:33.748 --> 17:35.706
I'm trying to help you.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.273
But if you don't
tell me the truth,

17:37.317 --> 17:39.145
the cops are gonna be
all over you.

17:45.325 --> 17:46.935
You got hard.

17:46.978 --> 17:48.719
I grew up.

17:48.763 --> 17:50.504
I had to.

17:50.547 --> 17:51.940
I have so many questions.

17:51.983 --> 17:53.768
-And I am answering them.
-They're all for Dani.

17:53.811 --> 17:56.249
How do you know this guy,
and what happened between you?

17:56.292 --> 17:58.164
-What are you doing?
-Agreeing with you.

17:58.207 --> 17:59.687
He's exhibiting stress reactions

17:59.730 --> 18:01.906
a profiler could spot
from space.

18:01.950 --> 18:03.256
Yo, I don't care
who you're rolling with,

18:03.299 --> 18:04.605
I'm not scared,
and I didn't kill...

18:04.648 --> 18:06.520
Desir? I know.

18:06.563 --> 18:09.523
You're posturing,
pretending to be hard.

18:09.566 --> 18:11.002
'Cause drug dealers are scary.

18:11.046 --> 18:13.744
Problem is you're not a killer.

18:13.788 --> 18:18.009
Dani's been telling me that
all day, and now I see it.

18:18.053 --> 18:19.924
DANI:
What really happened

18:19.968 --> 18:22.013
with you and Desir?

18:22.057 --> 18:24.538
I can't help you
if you don't tell me the truth.

18:24.581 --> 18:26.670
Desir was my friend.

18:28.324 --> 18:30.239
I loved him like a brother.

18:32.328 --> 18:34.809
Tell your people
I didn't do this.

18:35.897 --> 18:36.854
[woman screams]

18:36.898 --> 18:38.552
-[rapid gunfire]
-Get down!

18:38.595 --> 18:40.162
[people screaming, clamoring]

18:40.206 --> 18:42.251
Let's go! Keep your head down!

18:47.430 --> 18:48.431
[coughing]

18:50.346 --> 18:51.347
[coughing continues]

18:51.391 --> 18:53.393
DANI:
Bright, you good?

18:58.833 --> 19:01.096
-[sirens wailing]
-[police radio chatter]

19:01.140 --> 19:02.445
What the hell were you thinking?

19:02.489 --> 19:03.968
I knew that Estimé
would talk to me.

19:04.012 --> 19:05.405
-I made a call.
-Before we had a warrant.

19:05.448 --> 19:06.449
That's not a call.

19:06.493 --> 19:08.364
That is disobeying
a direct order.

19:08.408 --> 19:10.845
And Estimé's now... where?

19:10.888 --> 19:13.369
I know what this looks like,
but Estimé did not kill Desir.

19:13.413 --> 19:15.197
He is in way over his head.

19:15.241 --> 19:17.982
Dani's right.
He didn't do this.

19:18.026 --> 19:20.681
But I have a question.

19:20.724 --> 19:23.249
Why is everyone
moving in slow motion?

19:26.687 --> 19:28.123
You okay, Bright?

19:30.865 --> 19:35.174
When my father was arrested,
you helped to fill that void.

19:37.437 --> 19:41.267
You showed me
what a good man looks like.

19:41.310 --> 19:43.312
What a good man is.

19:46.446 --> 19:48.056
He's high as a kite.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.233
I'm higher than a kite.

19:51.277 --> 19:54.845
Estimé's stash exploded on him
during gunfire.

19:54.889 --> 19:56.586
Oh.

19:56.630 --> 19:59.154
What about you?

19:59.198 --> 20:00.895
I'm fine.

20:00.938 --> 20:03.637
-Yeah?
-I promise.

20:03.680 --> 20:05.682
Good.

20:07.902 --> 20:09.077
[Gil sighs]

20:09.120 --> 20:11.079
Take him home.

20:11.122 --> 20:12.602
What? We are in the...

20:12.646 --> 20:14.517
If you can't behave like a cop,
try babysitting

20:14.561 --> 20:16.127
till he comes down.

20:17.738 --> 20:19.305
JT and I have work to do.

20:21.524 --> 20:23.134
[lock clicks, door opens]

20:23.178 --> 20:24.962
[sighs] All right,
the best thing you can do

20:25.006 --> 20:26.486
for the next seven hours or so,

20:26.529 --> 20:28.314
just stay calm
and drink lots of water.

20:28.357 --> 20:30.925
Or... we throw axes!

20:30.968 --> 20:32.666
-What?
-You and me.

20:32.709 --> 20:34.276
Broad-bladed axes.

20:34.320 --> 20:36.844
I have five.

20:36.887 --> 20:39.455
No, six.

20:39.499 --> 20:40.891
Doesn't matter.
We have plenty.

20:40.935 --> 20:42.110
No.

20:42.153 --> 20:43.503
["Mack the Knife"
by Bobby Darin playing]

20:43.546 --> 20:45.113
Wow! God, this feeling!

20:45.156 --> 20:46.897
My-my neurons are on fire.

20:46.941 --> 20:50.684
You know, people say
that dopamine triggers pleasure.

20:50.727 --> 20:54.905
But really, it's about desire.

20:54.949 --> 20:56.342
Want to dance?

20:56.385 --> 20:57.995
Bright, I'm two seconds away

20:58.039 --> 20:59.388
from kicking you
in the business.

20:59.432 --> 21:01.390
And business is good.

21:01.434 --> 21:03.914
Answer me this, though.

21:03.958 --> 21:06.134
♪ You know when
that shark bites...♪

21:06.177 --> 21:08.745
No. No, lost it.

21:08.789 --> 21:10.312
Ah, my short-term memory
is just...

21:10.356 --> 21:12.532
Okay. Why don't you go throw
some water on your face,

21:12.575 --> 21:14.403
and I'm gonna make you
something to eat.

21:14.447 --> 21:15.535
Right.

21:15.578 --> 21:19.321
Right. Let's make...

21:19.365 --> 21:20.975
crumble.

21:21.018 --> 21:22.150
Grilled cheese?

21:23.499 --> 21:26.937
You know what?
I will never forget this.

21:26.981 --> 21:30.158
-I'm pretty sure you will.
-Thank you.

21:30.201 --> 21:32.421
For taking care of me.

21:33.379 --> 21:35.511
What are friends for?

21:35.555 --> 21:38.558
Wait. We're friends?

21:38.601 --> 21:39.646
Really?

21:40.864 --> 21:43.476
N-No. Not--

21:43.519 --> 21:46.392
I mean, not really,
but not-not yet.

21:46.435 --> 21:49.133
I'm out of practice
with friends.

21:49.177 --> 21:51.527
With companionship.

21:51.571 --> 21:53.355
-That's all right.
-[sighs]

21:53.399 --> 21:57.141
I... I don't have
a lot of friends, either.

21:57.185 --> 22:00.493
I got... issues with trust.

22:00.536 --> 22:03.234
I can't really go there anymore.

22:03.278 --> 22:05.106
You can trust me.

22:07.804 --> 22:10.720
[gasps] I have Jarlsberg!

22:10.764 --> 22:15.508
And a particularly stinky
Brie de Meaux.

22:17.684 --> 22:19.425
Let's do grilled cheese!

22:19.468 --> 22:21.514
Oh. 'Kay.

22:21.557 --> 22:23.167
Go wash up. I'm on it.

22:23.211 --> 22:25.953
-With the...?
-I am on it.

22:25.996 --> 22:27.041
Okay.

22:28.608 --> 22:30.914
[door opens, closes]

22:32.002 --> 22:33.613
[water splashes]

22:33.656 --> 22:36.093
[breathes deeply]

22:36.137 --> 22:37.530
[chuckles]

22:39.706 --> 22:41.621
[chain clinking]

22:41.664 --> 22:42.839
Hmm?

22:50.847 --> 22:53.807
♪ Now that Mackie's♪

22:53.850 --> 22:56.418
♪ Back in town♪

22:56.462 --> 22:59.073
♪ I said, Jenny Diver♪

22:59.116 --> 23:02.032
♪ Oh, Suky Tawdry♪

23:02.076 --> 23:04.818
♪ Look out to Miss Lotte Lenya♪

23:04.861 --> 23:08.038
-[panting]
-♪ And old Lucy Brown♪

23:08.082 --> 23:11.259
[slowing, distorting]:
♪ Yes, that line forms♪

23:11.302 --> 23:14.001
-Bright, you good?
-♪ On the right, babe ♪

23:14.044 --> 23:18.701
-♪ Now that Mackie's...♪
-[scratching]

23:20.616 --> 23:24.315
[whispers]:
No. No.

23:24.359 --> 23:26.361
[music slows, stops]

23:28.885 --> 23:32.454
[chain clinking]

23:32.498 --> 23:34.891
[woman whimpering]

23:36.502 --> 23:38.504
[quietly]:
It's not real.

23:43.160 --> 23:45.119
[panting]

23:46.686 --> 23:47.687
DANI:
Bright, you good?

23:47.730 --> 23:48.905
-[rattling]
-[woman screaming]

23:52.431 --> 23:53.519
[whispers]:
No.

23:55.564 --> 23:57.697
-[eerie scream]
-[muffled grunting]

23:57.740 --> 23:59.481
Bright?

24:00.743 --> 24:02.484
[panting]

24:09.186 --> 24:11.188
♪

24:14.757 --> 24:16.280
Dad?

24:16.324 --> 24:17.978
[sighs]

24:18.021 --> 24:19.458
Not exactly.

24:21.372 --> 24:24.724
This isn't real.
You're not real.

24:24.767 --> 24:26.334
Yet, and here I am.

24:26.377 --> 24:28.510
Nestled nicely between
your basal ganglia

24:28.554 --> 24:30.947
-and your cerebellum.
-Malcolm, my boy.

24:30.991 --> 24:32.645
Wearing your dad's cardigan.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.516
Nobody ever said
the subconscious was subtle.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.649
I'm high. I haven't slept.

24:36.692 --> 24:38.520
[whispers]:
Sweet dreams, my love.

24:38.564 --> 24:40.348
-That's why this is happening.
-Sure.

24:40.391 --> 24:42.568
Would you like
some flannel PJs?

24:42.611 --> 24:44.178
Perhaps a glass of warm milk?

24:44.221 --> 24:46.136
Let me out of here!

24:46.180 --> 24:47.747
-[cell door rattles]
-Don't you get it?

24:47.790 --> 24:50.532
We're all in here together.

24:50.576 --> 24:52.142
I'm only trying to show you
the truth about yourself.

24:52.186 --> 24:53.535
They call you a monster.

24:53.579 --> 24:54.754
You're a hallucination.

24:54.797 --> 24:58.148
I'm your subconscious.
Your ego. Your id.

24:58.192 --> 24:59.759
The Ghost of Christmas Past.

24:59.802 --> 25:02.196
Call me whatever you want.

25:02.239 --> 25:03.414
Just stop ignoring me!

25:03.458 --> 25:04.546
[screams]

25:04.590 --> 25:07.549
Buddy, I get it.

25:07.593 --> 25:08.768
These nightmares
you're having...

25:08.811 --> 25:10.770
nightmares you're having
are rough.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.598
-YOUNG BRIGHT: What's in here?
-Fragments of this,

25:12.641 --> 25:14.556
bits of that... bits of that.

25:14.600 --> 25:16.123
That station wagon.

25:16.166 --> 25:17.428
What did Dad do?

25:18.647 --> 25:21.389
-What did wedo?
-[screams]

25:21.432 --> 25:23.913
What you need is context.
Am I right?

25:23.957 --> 25:27.221
Something to help you stitch
all this crazy together.

25:27.264 --> 25:28.614
DANI:
Bright?

25:30.224 --> 25:31.747
I remember that.

25:31.791 --> 25:35.272
After he was arrested,
Mom burned all of the photos

25:35.316 --> 25:37.971
-and mementos of Dad. Whoosh.
-Get him out of here.

25:38.014 --> 25:40.800
Proof of his existence,
up in smoke.

25:40.843 --> 25:42.279
[knocking on door]

25:42.323 --> 25:44.804
-But you hid this box from her.
-DANI: Bright, you good?

25:44.847 --> 25:47.415
Under your childhood bed.

25:49.025 --> 25:50.766
-Find it. It'll help.
-[knocking]

25:50.810 --> 25:52.594
-DANI: Bright?
-Here.

25:52.638 --> 25:53.682
So you don't forget.

25:54.640 --> 25:56.990
DANI:
Bright? Bright?

25:57.033 --> 25:59.209
-[screaming]
-Relax.

25:59.253 --> 26:00.776
-Relax. Bright, calm down.
-[hyperventilating]

26:00.820 --> 26:02.386
Calm-- Hey, hey. Bright!

26:02.430 --> 26:04.040
[Bright screaming]

26:05.259 --> 26:06.652
[exhales]

26:13.223 --> 26:15.704
["Here Comes That Rainy Day
Feeling Again" by The Fortunes]

26:15.748 --> 26:18.228
BRIGHT:
Morning! Coffee?

26:18.272 --> 26:21.623
-I'm good. [clears throat]
-How did you sleep?

26:21.667 --> 26:23.843
On a counter.

26:25.671 --> 26:26.846
[groans softly]

26:26.889 --> 26:28.717
-Why is my jaw killing me?
-[pouring drink]

26:30.850 --> 26:32.242
I punched you.

26:32.286 --> 26:34.810
[laughs] It worked.

26:34.854 --> 26:36.812
I slept five hours.

26:36.856 --> 26:38.858
I should have you slug me
every night.

26:41.861 --> 26:44.864
♪ And soon my tears, they will
be falling like rain...♪

26:44.907 --> 26:46.866
I could tell
last night was hard.

26:46.909 --> 26:49.695
Seeing Estimé.

26:49.738 --> 26:52.785
What was he like
when you first met?

26:52.828 --> 26:56.266
When I was undercover,
I infiltrated Desir's crew.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.616
A hostess girl?

26:58.704 --> 27:02.229
We sold drinks, drugs.

27:02.272 --> 27:06.233
Most of the girls, they came
from Haiti after the earthquake.

27:06.276 --> 27:08.844
I managed to get close to him,
gather evidence.

27:10.106 --> 27:12.500
But everything went sideways.

27:12.543 --> 27:13.936
Estimé made you.

27:15.721 --> 27:17.505
We got too close.

27:18.854 --> 27:20.551
He kept it a secret.

27:20.595 --> 27:22.771
Never told anyone else
I was a cop.

27:24.425 --> 27:25.774
And then he saved me.

27:28.559 --> 27:30.083
[gasping]

27:30.126 --> 27:31.519
BRIGHT:
You OD'd.

27:31.562 --> 27:35.131
That's why Gil was worried
about you around drugs.

27:35.175 --> 27:36.698
Did you get hooked undercover?

27:36.742 --> 27:39.309
I thought that it made me
extra qualified,

27:39.353 --> 27:42.138
but it just... it just
made me extra stupid.

27:43.749 --> 27:46.099
When I hit bottom,
Estimé was the only one

27:46.142 --> 27:47.883
in Desir's crew who cared.

27:47.927 --> 27:49.929
He took me to the hospital.

27:49.972 --> 27:52.322
If it wasn't for him, I...

27:55.238 --> 27:57.458
That's how I know
he didn't do this.

28:00.940 --> 28:01.941
[knocking on door]

28:04.204 --> 28:06.206
-Morning.
-Morning.

28:07.773 --> 28:09.383
Our boy back to normal?

28:09.426 --> 28:11.472
Ah, yeah, his version of it.

28:12.821 --> 28:16.172
-Look, Gil, I...
-I know what Estimé did for you.

28:16.216 --> 28:18.348
And I understand you wanting
to protect him, but...

28:18.392 --> 28:21.569
He's a suspect, and I
shouldn't have broken rank.

28:21.612 --> 28:23.832
I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

28:23.876 --> 28:25.573
Make it up to me.

28:25.616 --> 28:28.141
We think Saulo was behind
the shooting at the club.

28:28.184 --> 28:29.751
JT is running down his crew.

28:29.795 --> 28:31.622
How do you know it's Saulo?

28:31.666 --> 28:34.147
We caught one of Estimé's
hostesses leaving the club

28:34.190 --> 28:36.889
with a semiautomatic; traced it
back to the Dominicans.

28:36.932 --> 28:38.978
Okay. Let me talk to her.

28:46.028 --> 28:48.901
Thank you, Mrs. Whitly.
You are incredibly generous.

28:48.944 --> 28:52.252
[chuckles]
Please. It's Jessica.

28:52.295 --> 28:54.950
Maybe it's best
if I do contribute anonymously.

28:54.994 --> 28:57.648
The Whitly name doesn't exactly
scream victims' rights.

28:58.693 --> 29:00.086
We can accommodate that.

29:01.652 --> 29:03.785
I just... I have to ask.

29:03.829 --> 29:05.787
You were a Milton
before you married.

29:05.831 --> 29:08.964
-Mm.
-That's practically royalty
in this city.

29:09.008 --> 29:12.751
Why did you keep it "Whitly"?
Hisname?

29:15.405 --> 29:19.453
Well, I... had been a Whitly
longer than I'd been a Milton.

29:19.496 --> 29:22.238
And I'd done a lot of good
as a Whitly.

29:22.282 --> 29:25.459
I let that man
take so much from me.

29:25.502 --> 29:27.200
I wasn't gonna give him that.

29:27.243 --> 29:29.245
That is amazing.
I love you.

29:29.289 --> 29:32.596
[laughs]:
Yes. Oh, well.

29:32.640 --> 29:34.598
If only we were sophomores
at Wellesley.

29:34.642 --> 29:36.644
-Oh. Okay.
-[both laughing]

29:36.687 --> 29:38.037
BRIGHT [in distance]:
Mother! I'm back.

29:38.080 --> 29:41.170
Don't worry.
I'm not after your barbiturates.

29:41.214 --> 29:42.824
I have company, dear.

29:42.868 --> 29:44.217
Oh.

29:44.260 --> 29:46.045
Uh...

29:46.088 --> 29:48.699
-Uh, hi.
-Hi.

29:50.745 --> 29:53.879
I just need to grab something
from upstairs.

29:53.922 --> 29:55.445
Um, box of old stuff

29:55.489 --> 29:57.447
-I kept under my bed.
-What old stuff?

29:57.491 --> 30:00.450
Uh, pictures.
Maybe a two-dollar bill.

30:00.494 --> 30:01.843
You know, memories.

30:01.887 --> 30:04.063
That we want to remember?

30:04.106 --> 30:07.022
A good amount of drugs
exploded in my face last night.

30:07.066 --> 30:09.851
Long story, work related.

30:09.895 --> 30:11.722
But it led to a breakthrough
of sorts.

30:13.768 --> 30:16.205
If there were a secret shoebox

30:16.249 --> 30:18.860
where you stored memories
of your father...

30:18.904 --> 30:20.731
I never said it was a shoebox.

30:22.124 --> 30:24.953
Whatever kind of box it was,

30:24.997 --> 30:27.738
it went up the chimney
with the rest of his things.

30:30.045 --> 30:32.918
Sorry for the interruption.

30:32.961 --> 30:34.745
[sighs]

30:34.789 --> 30:37.270
Eve, this is Malcolm.

30:37.313 --> 30:38.880
My son.

30:38.924 --> 30:40.926
Pleasure to meet you, Malcolm.

30:40.969 --> 30:43.232
JESSICA:
Eve fights
global human trafficking.

30:43.276 --> 30:45.887
I'm giving her all of our money.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.367
Thank God.

30:47.410 --> 30:48.803
And what do you do?

30:48.847 --> 30:51.719
-I'm in law enforcement.
-Let's not dwell on that.

30:51.762 --> 30:54.330
Yeah, it's mostly
boring office work.

30:54.374 --> 30:57.681
With exploding drugs?

30:57.725 --> 31:00.771
That doesn't sound...
boring to me.

31:00.815 --> 31:02.904
Yeah. Well... [chuckles]

31:02.948 --> 31:05.080
It's not always... boring.

31:05.124 --> 31:06.125
[chuckles]

31:12.000 --> 31:14.916
-Hey.
-I remember you.

31:14.960 --> 31:17.092
-From the club.
-Mm-hmm.

31:17.136 --> 31:18.920
So you're a cop now?

31:18.964 --> 31:20.487
I was a cop then.

31:20.530 --> 31:22.315
Had me fooled.

31:22.358 --> 31:24.099
What happened to Estimé
after I left?

31:24.143 --> 31:26.014
H-How did he get
dragged into this?

31:26.058 --> 31:27.537
Desir got to him.

31:27.581 --> 31:29.757
Then Estimé started
making real money,

31:29.800 --> 31:30.932
but his heart wasn't in it.

31:30.976 --> 31:34.109
Then why did he stay?

31:34.153 --> 31:37.765
Fabiola. A hostess
who worked with us.

31:37.808 --> 31:39.941
She was amazing.

31:39.985 --> 31:41.769
Pretty.

31:41.812 --> 31:44.554
That girl could do hair
like it was art.

31:47.166 --> 31:48.994
He fell for her hard.

31:51.605 --> 31:52.954
What happened to her?

32:05.619 --> 32:07.577
BRIGHT:
What did you find out?

32:07.621 --> 32:11.799
Estimé-- he fell for
one of Desir's hostesses.

32:11.842 --> 32:13.540
Fabiola Cadichon.

32:13.583 --> 32:15.803
Let me guess.

32:15.846 --> 32:17.848
Desir didn't want
to give her up.

32:19.850 --> 32:22.375
Estimé begged him.

32:22.418 --> 32:25.682
Desir, he-he didn't
take the rejection well,

32:25.726 --> 32:28.990
so he sent Fabiola
to mule heroin.

32:29.034 --> 32:33.212
Balloon burst and she died.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.086
[sighs]

32:40.088 --> 32:41.698
I'm sorry.

32:41.742 --> 32:44.223
I was right.

32:44.266 --> 32:46.703
Estimé wouldn't kill
for turf or product.

32:46.747 --> 32:49.228
This was about love.

32:49.271 --> 32:51.491
Check the awning.

32:53.145 --> 32:55.147
Fabiola had a gift for hair.

32:55.190 --> 32:57.192
He bought it for her.

32:58.846 --> 33:00.152
Solid profile.

33:00.195 --> 33:03.068
I learned from the best.

33:03.111 --> 33:05.026
Thanks.

33:05.070 --> 33:07.289
I meant Gil.

33:07.333 --> 33:08.769
[chuckles]

33:10.336 --> 33:14.122
He used to say,
"Police work is patience."

33:15.515 --> 33:18.126
Him and JT
are pulling a warrant.

33:18.170 --> 33:20.215
[chuckles]

33:20.259 --> 33:22.652
What?

33:22.696 --> 33:25.873
He used to tell me
the same thing when I was a kid,

33:25.916 --> 33:27.875
bored on some stakeout.

33:27.918 --> 33:31.096
"Police work is patience."

33:31.139 --> 33:33.837
He used to take you
on stakeouts?

33:33.881 --> 33:37.058
Mm, people have said
my childhood was weird.

33:37.102 --> 33:38.929
I don't see it.

33:42.455 --> 33:43.760
What?

33:43.804 --> 33:45.501
I...

33:47.503 --> 33:49.897
I just always thought
we were so different.

33:49.940 --> 33:52.117
Turns out Gil saved us both.

33:57.600 --> 34:00.734
Hold on. I got a mark.

34:00.777 --> 34:03.519
That's Trini. She takes care
of the hostesses.

34:03.563 --> 34:06.696
Looks like she's about to
take care of someone else.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.568
Gil, it's Powell.

34:08.611 --> 34:12.311
I think I got Estimé.
624 Glenwood Road.

34:12.354 --> 34:14.008
Wait for backup.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.967
Estimé won't hurt me.
I know that.

34:17.011 --> 34:19.144
Still...

34:19.187 --> 34:21.581
you don't have to
face him alone.

34:21.624 --> 34:23.191
I think I do.

34:29.328 --> 34:32.983
-Estimé.
-We don't take walk-ins, Dani.

34:33.027 --> 34:34.811
We know about Fabiola.

34:34.855 --> 34:36.987
Fabiola is dead.

34:39.555 --> 34:41.296
I bought this whole thing
for her.

34:41.340 --> 34:43.124
It was her dream.

34:43.168 --> 34:47.172
To have a shop,
cut hair, have kids.

34:48.869 --> 34:51.524
I used to have big dreams.

34:51.567 --> 34:53.830
Then I met Fabiola,

34:53.874 --> 34:57.138
and all I wanted to do was make
her little dreams come true.

34:57.182 --> 34:59.227
But Desir wouldn't let her go.

35:00.576 --> 35:02.535
He killed her,
so you killed him.

35:02.578 --> 35:06.234
ESTIMEÉ:
No. He made a mistake.

35:06.278 --> 35:08.323
But he was like a brother.
I didn't kill him.

35:08.367 --> 35:09.803
I couldn't kill anyone.

35:09.846 --> 35:13.241
You think I want this, Xavier?
To bring you in?

35:14.286 --> 35:16.723
I don't.

35:16.766 --> 35:18.681
But you made your choice.

35:20.248 --> 35:22.076
BRIGHT:
These are waterproof.

35:22.120 --> 35:24.078
What?

35:24.122 --> 35:27.081
Desir-- his chest
was clean of blood

35:27.125 --> 35:28.256
because he was wearing

35:28.300 --> 35:31.172
an outer layer
when his throat was cut.

35:31.216 --> 35:33.392
He was wearing one of these.

35:36.264 --> 35:38.266
Where did Fabiola
learn to cut hair?

35:40.050 --> 35:41.400
It's a skill.

35:44.054 --> 35:45.230
Who taught her?

35:45.273 --> 35:47.754
ESTIMEÉ:
Her mother, back in the islands.

35:47.797 --> 35:49.234
I never met her.

35:54.064 --> 35:55.501
BRIGHT:
Yes, you did.

35:57.416 --> 35:59.026
[grunting]

35:59.069 --> 36:00.114
-Drop it!
-ESTIMEÉ: What the...

36:01.724 --> 36:03.117
BRIGHT:
Don't move, Estimé.

36:03.161 --> 36:05.119
Meet Trini Cadichon.

36:06.860 --> 36:08.296
Fabiola's mother.

36:09.863 --> 36:12.257
-Don't do it, Trini.
-What'd you do, Trini?

36:12.300 --> 36:13.214
[Trini gasps]

36:13.258 --> 36:16.435
You cut Desir's hair, too.

36:16.478 --> 36:19.133
He was wearing one of these
when you slit his throat.

36:20.439 --> 36:22.223
Caught the blood
as you took his tongue.

36:24.312 --> 36:28.273
Desir put Fabiola
on that plane...

36:30.188 --> 36:32.494
...my baby,

36:32.538 --> 36:35.410
with his poison inside her.

36:35.454 --> 36:37.630
It wasn't my fault.

36:37.673 --> 36:40.676
You didn't stop Desir.

36:42.330 --> 36:46.116
Now I have nothing,
not even a grave

36:46.160 --> 36:48.728
-for my love.
-Where is Fabiola? Her body?

36:48.771 --> 36:51.121
Desir left her
in the Meadowlands.

36:51.165 --> 36:54.255
Trini, he knows
where Fabiola is.

36:54.299 --> 36:56.953
You kill him, that goes, too.

36:56.997 --> 37:00.261
But if you let him go,
I promise you,

37:00.305 --> 37:01.654
we will find your little girl.

37:01.697 --> 37:03.438
[breath trembling]

37:03.482 --> 37:05.484
And she can finally rest...

37:07.529 --> 37:09.357
...in peace.

37:11.316 --> 37:12.317
Trini.

37:13.753 --> 37:16.059
[tires screeching]

37:16.103 --> 37:17.626
Who is that? Backup?

37:17.670 --> 37:21.456
-No. It has to be Saulo.
-They found me.

37:21.500 --> 37:24.329
-They're here to kill me, too.
You might as well do it, Trini.
-[Trini grunts]

37:24.372 --> 37:25.504
Shut up, Estimé!

37:25.547 --> 37:26.418
[grunts]

37:26.461 --> 37:28.942
Trini, what do you think?

37:28.985 --> 37:31.118
DANI:
It's up to you.

37:31.161 --> 37:35.209
What's more important, revenge
or burying your daughter?

37:37.951 --> 37:39.692
[groans]

37:43.348 --> 37:45.001
First person
to walk out that door...

37:50.224 --> 37:51.399
Wait.

37:51.443 --> 37:53.445
She's a cop.

37:57.536 --> 37:59.146
Detective Powell, is it?

37:59.189 --> 38:01.148
What are you doing here, Saulo?

38:01.191 --> 38:03.368
Making a social call.

38:03.411 --> 38:06.632
And what brings you out
to this fine corner of Flatbush?

38:08.155 --> 38:10.375
Here to see Estimé, I assume.

38:14.292 --> 38:18.252
-What's all this blood?
-He's dead.

38:18.296 --> 38:20.907
Killed by the hairdresser
who took out Desir.

38:20.950 --> 38:22.952
Daughter died
moving product for them.

38:22.996 --> 38:25.346
I guess it was revenge.

38:25.390 --> 38:27.392
[sirens wailing]

38:31.221 --> 38:33.049
Care to stay
and make a statement?

38:33.093 --> 38:35.748
No, I think we'll be going,
Detective.

38:35.791 --> 38:37.227
It's getting late.

38:38.533 --> 38:39.795
-See you around.
-[engine starts]

38:39.839 --> 38:42.232
Better hope not.

38:43.451 --> 38:45.018
Let's roll.

38:53.592 --> 38:56.856
She's really buried
in the Meadowlands?

38:56.899 --> 38:58.858
Yup.

38:58.901 --> 39:01.600
You'll find Fabiola...

39:01.643 --> 39:03.950
here.

39:03.993 --> 39:06.300
You really gonna
get her buried right?

39:06.344 --> 39:10.783
Trini may be going to jail,
but I made a promise.

39:10.826 --> 39:12.393
Her daughter will get
a proper burial.

39:16.092 --> 39:17.093
[knocks]

39:22.882 --> 39:25.624
Okay, you got to go.

39:27.669 --> 39:30.672
Saulo thinks you're dead.
You need to stay that way.

39:30.716 --> 39:33.632
This is your chance to get out,

39:33.675 --> 39:35.285
away from that life.

39:35.329 --> 39:39.333
You really found a way
to put it all behind you, huh?

39:40.465 --> 39:42.771
Yeah, I did.

39:42.815 --> 39:44.382
Now it's your turn.

39:45.818 --> 39:47.515
Thank you.

39:53.347 --> 39:54.479
[sighs softly]

40:00.702 --> 40:03.575
[Bright clears throat]

40:03.618 --> 40:05.490
Peace offering.

40:05.533 --> 40:07.535
Freshly brewed Earl Grey tea.

40:09.711 --> 40:12.018
I love Earl Grey.

40:12.061 --> 40:14.107
[chuckles]

40:14.150 --> 40:15.935
I know.

40:15.978 --> 40:17.676
It's the aroma, isn't it?

40:19.939 --> 40:22.115
Think you mentioned
your grandma used to make it...

40:24.117 --> 40:27.120
Damn, I'm doing it again,
aren't I?

40:27.163 --> 40:30.079
You could always just ask.

40:30.123 --> 40:32.691
Okay. Friend.

40:32.734 --> 40:34.388
What is it?

40:34.432 --> 40:37.609
You've saved Estimé,
caught the killer.

40:39.001 --> 40:40.568
Why no celebration?

40:40.612 --> 40:44.311
They pulled me out August 2016.

40:44.354 --> 40:46.531
Fabiola arrived that October.

40:48.446 --> 40:51.666
You were Narcotics,
not a social worker.

40:51.710 --> 40:54.539
You couldn't have helped
Trini or Fabiola.

40:56.541 --> 40:58.368
I guess we'll never know, right?

41:02.982 --> 41:05.332
[sighs] That's the part
that kills me.

41:06.681 --> 41:08.640
What would Freud say to that?

41:08.683 --> 41:11.512
That unresolved
emotional conflicts

41:11.556 --> 41:13.732
often manifest in dreams,

41:13.775 --> 41:16.735
because a representation of the
true problem in our subconscious

41:16.778 --> 41:18.214
is far less damaging to the ego

41:18.258 --> 41:20.521
than processing the actual
object in the conscious...

41:23.785 --> 41:27.528
He'd also say, "Drink more tea.

41:27.572 --> 41:28.964
With friends."

41:47.722 --> 41:48.897
JESSICA [over voice mail]:
Malcolm,

41:48.941 --> 41:50.595
I sent Adolpho over with...

41:50.638 --> 41:52.771
[sighs] Well...

41:52.814 --> 41:54.337
I don't know
what you're looking for

41:54.381 --> 41:56.775
or why you insist
on doing this,

41:56.818 --> 41:58.603
but it is yours.

41:58.646 --> 42:00.822
-Good night.
-[line clicks]

42:00.866 --> 42:02.868
♪

42:10.440 --> 42:11.529
It'll help.

42:16.490 --> 42:17.839
[chuckles softly]

42:29.634 --> 42:31.636
♪

42:54.572 --> 42:56.748
MARTIN:
During this missing time...

42:58.010 --> 42:59.489
...what did you do?

43:02.318 --> 43:05.800
And why can't you remember?

43:07.062 --> 43:09.064
BRIGHT:
It's real.

43:47.320 --> 43:48.626
MAN:
Greg, move your head.
